{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Devolve ALL Welsh Tax revenue (Corporation & Individual) to The Welsh Government",
        "additional_details": "The reform seen in 2019 of allowing WG to levy ONLY the top 10pence of each Taxation band is woefully inadequate.\r\nI suggest ALL Tax revenue generated by Residents of Wales, Voters Registered in Wales, Businesses Registered in Wales, and, Those Businesses trading in Wales should pay their due tax directly to the Welsh Government",
        "background": "Individuals living in Wales pay the bulk of their Income Tax to the UK Government.\r\nCorporations registered in, and trading in Wales pay Corporation Tax to the UK Government.\r\nA proportion of this revenue is then paid back to Wales, this is inequitable and needs addressing.",
